OL,7,FMr Harrison added: "Had he not turned
OL,8,Fup for that flight he would not have
OL,9,Fbeen convicted of this offence. He
OL,10,Fwon't ever commit this offence again
OL,11,Fbecause of the loss of his job."
OL,13,FPentecost, of Basingstoke, was said to
OL,14,Fbe "terrified" at the prospect of
OL,15,Flosing his liberty and "mortified" at
OL,16,Fthe shame he had brought on himself.
